The configuration file for OpenShift using Nix would be written in the Nix expression language. This is a functional language that is used to define and configure software packages in Nix.

The exact contents of the configuration file will depend on your specific needs and requirements for your OpenShift installation. However, a basic configuration file might look something like this:
```
{ config, pkgs, ... }:

let
  openshiftVersion = "4.6.7";
  openshiftCluster = pkgs.openshift-cluster.buildOpenShift({
    version = openshiftVersion;
    apiServer = {
      extraArgs = {
        "service-account-signing-key-file" = "/etc/openshift/keys/service-account-signing-key.pem";
      };
    };
    controllers = {
      extraArgs = {
        "service-account-signing-key-file" = "/etc/openshift/keys/service-account-signing-key.pem";
      };
    };
    node = {
      extraArgs = {
        "service-account-signing-key-file" = "/etc/openshift/keys/service-account-signing-key.pem";
      };
    };
  });
in

{
  environment.systemPackages = [
    openshiftCluster
  ];
}
```
This configuration file defines a number of different components of the OpenShift cluster, including the API server, the node components, and the controllers. It also specifies the version of OpenShift to use, as well as some additional arguments that will be passed to the components when they are started.

Again, this is just a very basic example of a Nix configuration file for OpenShift. Your configuration file may look different, depending on your specific needs and requirements. If you need help creating a configuration file for your OpenShift installation, I would recommend consulting the NixOS manual or seeking help from the Nix community.

To add a program that generates the necessary SSL certificates and keys, runs `oc-adm`, and sets up `systemd` and `systemctl` to the previous Nixpkg configuration file, you could use the `postInstall` and `preConfigure` functions in the Nix expression language.

Here is an example of how this might look:
```
{ config, pkgs, ... }:

let
  openshiftVersion = "4.6.7";
  openshiftCluster = pkgs.openshift-cluster.buildOpenShift({
    version = openshiftVersion;
    apiServer = {
      extraArgs = {
        "service-account-signing-key-file" = "/etc/openshift/keys/service-account-signing-key.pem";
      };
    };
    controllers = {
      extraArgs = {
        "service-account-signing-key-file" = "/etc/openshift/keys/service-account-signing-key.pem";
      };
    };
    node = {
      extraArgs = {
        "service-account-signing-key-file" = "/etc/openshift/keys/service-account-signing-key.pem";
      };
    };
  });

  generateCertsAndKeys = pkgs.runCommand "generate-certs-and-keys" {
    buildInputs = [ pkgs.openssl ];
    installPhase = ''
      openssl req -x509 -sha256 -newkey rsa:4096 -nodes \
        -keyout /etc/openshift/keys/service-account-signing-key.pem \
        -out /etc/openshift/keys/service-account-signing-key.pem \
        -subj "/CN=service-accounts" \
        -days 3650
    '';
  };

  runOcAdm = pkgs.runCommand "run-oc-adm" {
    buildInputs = [ openshiftCluster ];
    installPhase = ''
      oc adm create-api-client-config \
        --client-dir /etc/openshift/keys \
        --signer-cert /etc/openshift/keys/service-account-signing-key.pem \
        --signer-key /etc/openshift/keys/service-account-signing-key.pem \
        --signer-serial /etc/openshift/keys/service-account-signing-key.serial
    '';
  };

in

{
  environment.systemPackages = [
    openshiftCluster
  ];

  system.postInstall = "generateCertsAndKeys";
  system.preConfigure = "runOcAdm";
  services.systemd.extraConfig = ''
    [Unit]
    Description=OpenShift API Server
    Requires=network-online.target
    After=network-online.target

    [Service]
    Type=notify
    WorkingDirectory=${openshiftCluster}/openshift-apiserver
    ExecStart=${openshiftCluster}/openshift-apiserver/openshift-apiserver
    Restart=on-failure
    LimitNOFILE=65536

    [Install]
```

